parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power train can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult or impossible to accelerate, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle makes unusual noises
the vehicle vibrates or shakes
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, making it difficult or impossible to stop, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The brakes squeak or make unusual noises
the brakes vibrate or pulse
the brakes feel soft or spongy
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear suspension can cause the vehicle to lose stability, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The rear of the vehicle falls or sags
the vehicle makes unusual noises from the rear
the vehicle vibrates or shakes
the vehicle is difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the bushings can cause the vehicle to make unusual noises, vibrate, or lose stability, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle makes unusual noises
the vehicle vibrates or shakes
the vehicle is difficult to control
the bushings wear out prematurely.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag sensor can lead to the airbag failing to deploy in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality. Additionally, faulty sensors can cause incorrect warnings or indicators, leading to driver distraction and potential accidents.
symptoms: The airbag warning light remains illuminated on the dashboard
the passenger airbag sensor indicator light comes on and will not turn off
the airbag fails to deploy in the event of a crash
incorrect warnings or indicators appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of a crash can increase the risk of injury or fatality to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The airbag does not deploy in the event of a crash
the driver and passengers are injured in a crash
the vehicle's airbag system fails to function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to suddenly and unexpectedly speed up, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
RPMs dramatically increase
the vehicle surges forward
the warning indicators on the instrument panel do not illuminate
the vehicle may continue to accelerate even when the brakes are applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning cruise control system can cause the vehicle to unexpectedly change speed, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The cruise control system automatically adjusts speed beyond normal operating procedures
the cruise control speed decreases or increases without warning
the cruise control system malfunctions when changing lanes
the cruise control system does not respond to adjustments.
